            "id": "c3bd261f296a47308696e",
            "questionText": "A car's battery is composed of four identical cells connected in series, with each cell having an electromotive force of $!$3\\,\\text{V}$!$. Calculate the total electromotive force $!$E_{total}$!$ of the car's battery.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "df7b2862d3b94fcd9dd0c",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling the formula that we use for combining electromotive forces (e.m.f.) in cells connected in series. Which one of the following formulas correctly represents the total e.m.f. for cells connected in series?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "320b0a47-989b-4366-9676-1f34e540ac09",
                        "b14dd40f-3728-4962-ae52-1fb9c050b293"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E = E_1 + E_2 + E_3 + E_4$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E = \\frac{E_1 + E_2 + E_3 + E_4}{4}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E = E_1 \\times E_2 \\times E_3 \\times E_4$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cd2cf38708b240228f7cd",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have identified how e.m.f.s add in series, let's calculate the total e.m.f. by multiplying the number of cells by the e.m.f. of one cell. What is the product when you multiply 4 by 3?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "12"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "V",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "320b0a47-989b-4366-9676-1f34e540ac09"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "adc6dd9232c24011b951f",
                    "stepText": "Now that you have computed the multiplication, this gives you the total electromotive force of the battery. Ensure that your final result represents the total e.m.f. of the series-connected cells in the battery.",
