        {
            "id": "f9d0611db2934bd2aacc6",
            "questionText": "A smart garden lighting system uses a Light-Dependent Resistor (LDR) in a potential divider circuit to switch on LED lamps at dusk. The potential divider is supplied by a $!$12\\text{ V}$!$ battery. The LDR is connected in series with a fixed resistor of $!$R_{fixed} = 200\\text{ }\\Omega$!$. When the ambient light intensity decreases to a certain level at dusk, the resistance of the LDR increases to $!$R_{LDR} = 400\\text{ }\\\\Omega$!$. Calculate the potential difference across the LDR at this light level.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "88c3ce4cc3c5440d9e778",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the formula that calculates the voltage across a resistor in a potential divider circuit. Which of the following formulas is the appropriate one for finding the voltage across the LDR?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "769fd15e-b379-43a1-b7a8-6c022fe74eca",
                        "9eb53fd6-048e-47f9-9abe-1cf126748480"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V_{LDR} = V \\times \\frac{R_{LDR}}{R_{fixed} + R_{LDR}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V_{LDR} = I \\times R_{LDR}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V_{LDR} = V - I \\times R_{LDR}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "5386277876604bb7b62f0",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, compute the total resistance in the circuit by adding the fixed resistor and the LDR resistances. What is the sum of $!$200\\Omega$!$ and $!$400\\Omega$!$?",
